ng with this new loot code.  I'm sorry, but I just don't see it.  Unless things drastically change when you get to level 60 as far as loot goes, I don't know what everyone is complaining about.<br>
<br>
At my current level (36), there are very few things I WANT that I can even get myself.  All of us are constantly trying to upgrade our equipment, and as a result most of us have bought stuff that we ourselves aren't even high enough level to attain on our own. (or at least not without a full group or more)  So, basically, by the time I get high enough level to kill the mobs that drop the loot I wanted 10 levels before, I don't want or need what they have and chances are, it's not worth nearly as much as I paid for it anyway.<br>
<br>
Basically, what I'm saying is...at level 60 you probably have MUCH better stuff than anything you could loot off a green or do a low level quest to attain.  On the off chance there is something that you really want that can only be looted from a green mob, then where is the harm in having to buy it for a change?  The only reason I see someone at level 60 wanting this stuff is to twink an alternate.  I don't see anything wrong with having to buy the stuff from lower level people to twink another character of yours...heck, most people do that anyway because it's faster and most of the stuff you want is very affordable.  You'll still be able to farm stuff in all the current zones (except the Warrens and Stonebrunt Mountains of course) and sell them for a profit to be able to buy stuff from the zones with the WLC.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I just don't see people level 55+ or whatever missing out on anything.  How often do you see people drooling over a drop that came from the Warrens?  Verant knows that if they put stuff that high level people really want on mobs they can't get loot from, they will get flamed beyond belief.  They know the player base is slowly rising to high levels.  I have a feeling that there won't be much decent loot at all in SoL on any mobs that aren't blue to level 55+, but I could be wrong.<br>
