<br>
1. No where in the policy does it state that players will have to buy quest loot and/or focus items. This was inferred by a number of the people here to back up their already flawed arguments. No doubt, Verant will make quest and/or No Drop items a special case as these wouldn't necessarily be &quot;farmed.&quot;<br>
<br>
2. In the numerous press releases following the announcement of SoL, Verant made it clear that the new expansion was to be a &quot;group of 6&quot; expansion, as opposed to Velious being a &quot;30+ people raid type&quot; expansion. Reasons for this are obvious - no race can actually begin in Velious. The press announcements for Velious all declared Velious as a place for &quot;hardcore, level 35+ players.&quot; SoL will feature the Vah`Siir class, who will begin on Luclin. It would be very troublesome if there were no places for the Vah`Siir to hunt on Luclin, and everyone who played a Vah`Siir had to get a wizard to port them to the Old World.<br>
